The paper proposes a procedure for designing controlled test problems for single-objective bilevel optimization, which is a topic related to optimization and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.OH (Optimization and Control) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also presents a standard test suite of problems, which involves data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well. The paper uses a nested bilevel evolutionary algorithm to solve the proposed test problems, which is a machine learning technique, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the different complexities that can be included in the test problems, which is related to artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category.
